As the Crown Prince's color, ''ōdan'' first appeared in the ''[[:en:Yōrō Code|Yōrō Code]]'' under the "Clothing Ordinance," where it was described as the fixed color for the Crown Prince's {{ill|Ceremonial dress|ja|礼服 (宮中)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ceremonial dress|qq=}}: "Crown Prince's [[:en:Formal wear|Formal attire]], formal [[:en:Raikan|Crown (headgear)]], '''ōdan robe''' (黄丹衣), ivory {{ill|Scepter|ja|牙笏|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Scepter|qq=}}, white {{ill|Hakama|ja|白袴|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hakama|qq=}}, white belt, and deep purple {{ill|Sha-ju|ja|紗褶|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sha-ju|qq=}}." Even today, the Crown Prince wears the ''Ōdan no hō'' (黄丹袍) during ceremonies such as the {{ill|Rittaishi|ja|立太子|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rittaishi|qq=}} (Investiture as Crown Prince) and {{ill|Japanese imperial wedding|ja|婚礼|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese imperial wedding|qq=}} ceremonies. According to the ''[[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]]'', ''ōdan'' dye was produced using {{ill|Safflower|ja|紅花|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Safflower|qq=}} and {{ill|Gardenia jasminoides|ja|梔子|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gardenia jasminoides|qq=}}, resulting in a strong reddish-orange hue. As the Crown Prince's exclusive color, ''ōdan'' was designated a [[:en:Forbidden colors (Japan)|Forbidden color]], prohibiting its use by others.
== Related Articles == * {{ill|Kōrozen|ja|黄櫨染|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōrozen|qq=}} * {{ill|Gardenia color|ja|梔子色|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gardenia color|qq=}} * {{ill|Shu-kasa color|ja|朱華色|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shu-kasa color|qq=}}
== References == * Kunio Fukuda, ''Suguwakaru Nihon no dentōshoku'' (すぐわかる 日本の伝統色), Tokyo Bijutsu, ISBN 4-8087-0784-5. * Yukio Yoshioka, ''Nihon no iro jiten'' (日本の色辞典), Shikosha, ISBN 4-87940-549-3.
